# arvo-hash

L2 hash-domain types and algorithm contracts. ContentHash aliases
arvo-bits Bits at 28 bits for call-site domain naming. Generic
streaming Hasher and HasherExt traits parameterise over BitWidth from
arvo L0 so downstream code stays algorithm-agnostic. Ships
`Fnv1a<const N: BitWidth>` as the first concrete Hasher with both
runtime trait form and const-fn `hash_const` entry usable in
compile-time positions. xxHash and CRC32 follow in later rounds.
`#![no_std]`, no alloc.
